snippet: Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri has taken the country by storm in a campaign that has gripped the media and visibly jolted the traditional political mainstream.
abstract: Pakistani preacher Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri has taken country by storm in campaign that has gripped news media and jolted traditional political mainstream; Qadri, who returned from Canada after living there for seven years, made his first mark with large rally in Lahore calling on Pres Asif Ali Zardari to resign to make way for caretaker administration led by technocrats.

byline.contributor: Salman Masood contributed reporting from Islamabad, and Waqar Gilani from Lahore, Pakistan.

lead_paragraph: Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri has taken the country by storm in a campaign that has gripped the media and visibly jolted the traditional political mainstream.

headline.main: A Fiery Preacher’s Arrival Shakes Pakistani Politics
headline.print_headline: A Fiery Preacher’s Arrival Shakes Pakistani Politics
